The paper deals with the problem of hinged dissections, which involves the folding and manipulation of polygons and polyhedra. This topic is closely related to computational geometry (cs.CG), as well as discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT), which are likely sub-categories for this paper. The paper also discusses the potential applications of hinged dissections to reconfigurable robotics and programmable matter, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and possibly other sub-categories such as computer vision (cs.CV) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
